# Rockads Frontend Standards

## Scope

- Apply these standards to all implementation and refactor tasks in this repository.
- Keep all code, comments, and user-facing text in English.

## Vue and Nuxt

- Use Vue 3 Composition API with `<script setup lang="ts">` for components.
- Prefer Nuxt auto-imported composables (`useRoute`, `useRouter`, `useAsyncData`) instead of manual imports when available.
- Keep components focused; extract reusable logic to composables under `app/composables` when logic grows.
- Avoid direct browser globals in SSR paths; gate browser-only access with `import.meta.client`.

## UI and shadcn-nuxt

- Follow a shadcn-first decision policy: reuse `app/components/ui` primitives first, then add shadcn-compatible primitives, and only then build custom UI.
- Reuse existing primitives in `app/components/ui` before creating new base UI components.
- Keep variant logic in `class-variance-authority` patterns when a component has multiple visual states.
- Use the configured shadcn component directory (`@/components/ui`) and current no-prefix setup.

## Motion and Animation

- Prefer `motion-v` for component-level motion and enter/exit transitions instead of custom animation utilities.
- Keep motion subtle and purposeful; avoid decorative animations that reduce readability or perceived performance.
- Respect reduced-motion preferences and provide non-animated fallbacks when motion is optional.
- Reuse shared timing and easing tokens/patterns; avoid ad-hoc per-component animation values.

## Tailwind CSS (v4)

- Use Tailwind utility classes and design tokens from `app/assets/css/tailwind.css`.
- Prefer semantic token utilities (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`) over hardcoded colors.
- Keep dark mode compatible by relying on tokenized classes and existing `dark` variant behavior.

## Linting and Formatting

- Use Oxlint + ESLint (`pnpm lint`) as source of truth for linting.
- Preserve tab indentation and double-quote style in JavaScript/TypeScript.
- Do not introduce new lint suppressions unless there is no practical alternative.

## Quality Guardrails

- Keep naming explicit and domain-driven; avoid vague names like `data`, `item`, `temp`.
- Prefer small, typed helpers over duplicated inline logic.
- Update or add minimal tests when behavior changes.
- Run `pnpm lint` (or `pnpm lint:fix` when needed) after substantive edits.
